{
  "texts": [
    "In this section we investigate how Hofstede's cultural dimensions have been reported in the literature to influence the requirements elicitation.",
    "Organizational structure within organizations in countries with high PDI reflects a superior-inferior power relationship (Hanisch and Corbitt 2007; Hofstede 2001).",
    "Decision-making and communication processes take hierarchical and bureaucratic forms.",
    "High PDI enables establishment of behavioral patterns by both requirements elicitation engineer and customer/user, and facilitates the alleviation of tensions between the involved parts.",
    "In high PDI countries power normally comes with the title, rank, and status within the organization or in the society (Söderman 2008)."
  ]
}